race.comment: SPEEDTAIL (1) settled midfield but struggled to get into the race last start when the on-pacers controlled and dominated. His form prior was very good so expect the horse is close to another win. He looks well placed here stepping to 1400m and dropping in grade. He can win. THE WIRRULLA BOY (5) was solid enough over 1100m first-up which is short of his best. Expect improvement second-up to 1400m. He looks a main danger, as does BOLTED IN (10) who looks ready to peak. He's drawn to get a soft run on or behind the speed. He's never won over 1400m but he might be ready for it now. Impossible to fault the form of THEBIGSOSSO (2), who is chasing three wins in a row, while BOWER BOY (3) can improve and is one at a bigger price for wider plays.
